I traveled the world with @johnmulaney this year on his #fromscratchtour. On the road we talked about our favorite things… comedy, show business, and what people in show business do with their money.  Every night I brought him on stage, I would say “the tour is called from scratch but this is the best he’s ever been.“ I stand by that.  Baby J is back on the streets! 

Now please slide to see why my kids will be opening for his next tour.

Happy 10th birthday to our hilarious human Funko Pop and always confident Mario enthusiast!  How has it been 10 years?! What is time? I really don’t understand.  But I’m very proud of the person he’s become. I just really wish he would sleep later.
This Sunday the roast of everyone’s favorite liar the one and only @whitneycummings streams on @onlyfans 🫡  And we finally get an answer to that constant question. “Is Whitney ok?” Nope.

This month I’ll be in LA!  Stamford!  Austin! & San Diego! Come to a show! I promise it will be the greatest night of your life!  LINK FOR TIX IN BIO!

I first discovered stand up comedy by watching A&E Evening at the Improv.  I was 10, and I decided I was gonna be a comedian. I just wasn't sure how. Then when I was 17, I went to LA on vacation and got to go see a show at the actual club. This was very exciting. 
As I walked in, Jay Mohr came out of the greenroom, saw me and my colorful shirt and said "Jesus did this kid just kill a couch?" A bunch of people laughed at me, and I loved it.  The host of MTVs Lip Service was making fun of me! 
We watched the show, and I got see Mitch Hedberg destroy and Keenan Ivory Wayans work out jokes for his talk show monologue. It was 1997 and I couldn't believe I was even there. 
Years later, I'm performing at the 2002 Montreal Comedy festival. After my set, the legendary Budd Friedman comes up to me and says he thinks I’m funny and when I move to LA I have to play his club.  And he kept his word. Budd booked me at the Hollywood Improv, Vegas Improv (where I bombed hard multiple times) and even the Lake Tahoe Improv (where I did better than Vegas but still not great.) But Budd would keep booking me, and 20 years later it feels very special to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the place that really started it all for me. So thank you, Budd, The Improv, and all the comedians that continue to make fun of my clothes.
